  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Partnerships for Democracy in Tunisia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the project is to empower young local non-governmental organizations in Tunisia, strengthen their internal infrastructure and their capacities for advocacy and public policy interventions, and assist in intensification of the dialogue between the civil society and the government institutions in Tunisia.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at supporting the emerging civil society in the post-revolution Tunisia by transfering experience of Slovakia and other countries in transition to democracy, process of building of a vibrant civil society and establishment of functioning mechanisms of consultation and cooperation between the state and the non-state actors.Among the activities planned there are trainings, study visits of the Tunisian CSOs in Slovakia and micro - granting scheme to support local advocacy initiatives</narrative>
  </description>
