   <description>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">In October 2012, 14 activists from organizations I Watch and OFIYYA attended a workshop in Bratislava where the took part in seminars aimed at civil advocacy, strategies of public interest promotion, communication with communities, public, media, and state institutions, as well as at public policy. Workshops for 54 civil activists from Tunisia took place in Tunis, Kairouan, Gafsa, and Houmt Souk on Djerba Island during November and December 2012. They were focused on advocacy activities, civil rights advocacy, and best practices of successful advocacy campaigns.</narrative>
   </description>
